# MeshCore Signed Plugin Release Flow

When the user provides a signed plugin zip path (TPC/TAK Signed) for **MeshCore**, perform this flow end-to-end:

1. Verify `main` is current and pushed on `atakmaps/TAK-MESHCORE`.
2. Inspect the zip and extract the signed APK (`ATAK-Plugin-Meshcore-*-tpc-*-civ-release.apk`).
3. Validate APK: `package: com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin`, `versionCode` / `versionName` match release intent.
4. **TPC-only APK** — use files from `TAK Signed/*.zip` (`-tpc-` in filename). Never deploy git-hash local builds from `TAK Submissions/` (ATAK marks them Incompatible).
5. Create/push tag `v<version>` on the release commit; create GitHub Release on **TAK-MESHCORE** with title **`TAK-MeshCore <version>`**, signed APK(s), and source zip(s) for each ATAK target submitted.
6. **Do not** deploy to `com.uvpro.plugin.apk` — that is UV-PRO only.

## Cloud deploy (per ATAK target)

**Always sequential** — scp APK first, then edit `generate_infz.py`, then regenerate. Never parallel scp + catalog update.

### ATAK 5.5.1

```bash
scp "$APK" root@31.220.30.74:/var/www/html/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin.apk
ssh root@31.220.30.74 "
  # Edit generate_infz.py: CATALOGS['5.5.1'] TAK-MeshCore version + version_code only
  python3 /var/www/html/plugins/generate_infz.py
"
```

### ATAK 5.6.0

```bash
scp "$APK" root@31.220.30.74:/var/www/html/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin-5.6.0.apk
ssh root@31.220.30.74 "
  # Edit generate_infz.py: CATALOGS['5.6.0'] TAK-MeshCore version + version_code only
  python3 /var/www/html/plugins/generate_infz.py
"
```

`generate_infz.py` writes `product.inf` + `product.infz` and refreshes `5.6.0/plugins/` symlinks automatically.

## Post-deploy verification (required)

```bash
# 5.6.0 catalog (ATAK 5.6 fetches product.inf, not .infz)
curl -fsS https://atakmaps.com/plugins/5.6.0/product.inf | grep com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin
curl -sI https://atakmaps.com/plugins/5.6.0/product.inf | head -3

# OTA download paths ATAK constructs for 5.6.0 catalog rows
curl -sI https://atakmaps.com/plugins/5.6.0/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin-5.6.0.apk | head -3
curl -sI https://atakmaps.com/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin-5.6.0.apk | head -3

# 5.5.1
curl -fsS https://atakmaps.com/plugins/5.5.1/product.inf | grep com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin
curl -sI https://atakmaps.com/plugins/5.5.1/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin.apk | head -3
```

Hash in `product.inf` must match `sha256sum` of the deployed APK. Do not report success until version, versionCode, hash, size, and URLs all match.

## TPC submission (before signing)

`tools/package-submission.sh` fails unless these are **committed** on `main`:

- `app/src/main/assets/atakmaps-ca.p12`
- `app/src/main/assets/isrg-root-x1.pem`

Same CA bundle as UV-PRO (`atakatak` / `meshcore_trust_bundle_p12_key` in strings.xml).

Dual ATAK builds: `./tools/build-submission-zips.sh` (separate `*-ATAK-5.5.1-*` and `*-ATAK-5.6.0-*` source zips).

Prefer explicit verification over assumptions. If any step fails, stop and report the exact blocker.
